ZH: 他不理我。
EN: He ignores me.

ZH: 我天天跟他说话，但是他总是不理我。
EN: I talk to him every day, but he always ignores me.

ZH: 她不理你只是因为她很忙。
EN: She ignores you because she is busy.

ZH: 我们跟他解释了很多次，但是他还是不理解。
EN: We explained to him many times, but he still doesn't understand.

ZH: 他不理会我的建议。
EN: He ignores my advice.

ZH: 请不要不理我。
EN: Please don't ignore me.

ZH: 他那么不理解你的感受。
EN: He is so oblivious to your feelings.

ZH: 她不理解我的痛苦。
EN: She does not understand my pain.

ZH: 你为什么总是不理我？
EN: Why do you always ignore me?

ZH: 我知道他不理解我们的决定。
EN: I know he doesn't understand our decision.

ZH: 他是个很不理智的人。
EN: He is a very irrational person.

ZH: 她是个很不理性的女孩。
EN: She is a very unreasonable girl.

ZH: 她的态度总是让我很不爽。
EN: Her attitude always annoys me.

ZH: 他一直把我当透明人。
EN: He always treats me like a transparent person.

ZH: 不要一直对我无视。
EN: Stop ignoring me all the time.

ZH: 他说他忙，其实他是不想理我。
EN: He says he is busy, but in fact, he just doesn't want to acknowledge me.

ZH: 你对我不理，我也不会再和你说话了。
EN: If you ignore me, I won't talk to you anymore.

ZH: 坐在那里不理我是一种不礼貌的表现。
EN: Sitting there ignoring me is rude.

ZH: 不理解对方的立场是导致冲突的主要原因之一。
EN: Not understanding the other person's position is one of the main reasons for conflicts.

ZH: 你总是不理会我的感受。
EN: You always ignore my feelings.
